modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve and set the floating-point rounding mode, using fegetround and fesetround. Operates on integer values representing rounding modes such as FE_TONEAREST and FE_DOWNWARD. Useful for controlling numerical precision in scientific computations or numerical analysis tasks.

Provides functions to retrieve and set the current floating-point rounding mode. Operates on the `rounding_mode` type, which specifies how floating-point operations are rounded. Used to control precision behavior in numerical computations, such as when implementing custom math algorithms or ensuring consistent results across platforms.
